  "signature": "ed25519:9a2c4f1b7e3d0a6c8f5b2e4d1c7a9f3b6e0d2c5a8f1b4e7d0c3a6f9b2e5d8c1",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for modelRiskLevel 3.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented V&V procedures and ISO 9001 quality management. FDA in-house scripts are version-controlled in a Git repository with peer-reviewed commit history. DePuy Synthes provided a software quality plan consistent with 21 CFR Part 820. All three modeling teams demonstrated adequate SQA documentation, achieving Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10 and Ansys verification manual were used to confirm correct implementation of linear elastic and contact mechanics formulations. Patch tests and cantilever beam benchmarks confirmed solver accuracy within 0.5% of analytical solutions for the relevant element types (SOLID186, CONTA174)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "A systematic mesh convergence study was performed across three refinement levels (coarse, medium, fine) for the pedicle screw shank and rod interface regions. Richardson extrapolation yielded a discretization error estimate of 1.2% for construct stiffness, well below the 10% acceptance bound. The fine mesh (element edge length ≤ 0.3 mm at stress concentrations) was selected for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver (PCG with incomplete Cholesky preconditioning) residual tolerances were set to 1e-8. Force and displacement convergence criteria were verified per Ansys best-practice guidelines. No solver divergence events were observed across the full N=11 simulation ensemble."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "A documented simulation protocol with step-by-step instructions was followed by all three modeling teams. Independent cross-checks were performed between FDA and DePuy Synthes results to identify any operator-induced discrepancies. No systematic use errors were identified; inter-analyst variability in QoI predictions was less than 2%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic constitutive models were applied to titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) components with material properties from ASTM B265 coupon testing. Contact interactions between screw head and rod were modeled with frictional contact (μ=0.2, Coulomb). The model form is well-established for metallic implant mechanics under quasi-static loading and is consistent with published literature."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs were derived from CAD files provided by DePuy Synthes and verified against dimensional measurements of physical specimens (tolerance ≤ 0.05 mm). Material properties were sourced from lot-specific coupon testing (E = 114 ± 2 GPa, ν = 0.34). Applied loads and boundary conditions replicated ASTM F1717 fixture geometry and displacement-controlled loading rate (25 mm/min)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested across two independent laboratories. All specimens were sourced from the same production lot, ensuring geometric and material consistency. Sample size was selected based on a power analysis targeting 80% power to detect a 5% difference in stiffness at α=0.05."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted strictly per ASTM F1717 at a single displacement rate (25 mm/min) and ambient temperature (23 ± 2 °C). Only one test condition was evaluated; the influence of loading rate variation and temperature extremes on construct behavior was not explored. This limitation results in an achieved level of 2, below the required level of 3 for this modelRiskLevel."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Simulation input parameters were mapped directly to experimental measurements: CAD geometry verified against specimen dimensions, material properties from same-lot coupon testing, and boundary conditions replicating physical fixture constraints. A parameter equivalency table was prepared and reviewed by all three modeling teams, confirming high fidelity between simulation and physical test configurations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics included percent difference in mean QoI values and the E/uval ratio per ASME V&V 40 Section 6. All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfied the pre-established 10% difference bound and E/uval < 1.96 threshold. Uncertainty in experimental measurements was propagated from load cell calibration (±0.5%) and displacement transducer accuracy (±0.1 mm)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
