      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly specified in ASTM F1717 and are the primary biomechanical endpoints used in regulatory submissions for pedicle screw systems. They are closely aligned with clinical performance indicators relevant to spinal fusion construct stability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for modelRiskLevel 3.",
      "rationale": "The validation team determined that the relevance of validation activities to the COU does not require formal assessment because the validation protocol was designed to be co-extensive with the COU by construction — the bench test replicates the exact ASTM F1717 loading scenario addressed in the COU, and no extrapolation beyond the validated domain is claimed. Accordingly, this factor was treated as self-evidently satisfied and no formal gradation exercise was performed. This reasoning was accepted by the credibility assessment team without escalation, though the factor remains ungraded in the formal record."
    }
