    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment concludes that the FEA modeling framework is sufficiently credible for the stated COU. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors were formally assessed; eleven achieved or exceeded their required levels. The Test conditions factor achieved Gradation 2 against a required level of 3, representing a known limitation acknowledged in the assessment. The Relevance of validation activities to the COU factor was not formally graded on the basis that the validation protocol was designed to be co-extensive with the COU; the team accepted this reasoning. All three QoIs satisfied pre-established acceptance bounds across N=11 constructs at two independent laboratories. The package is accepted for use in the regulatory submission supporting the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
